<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Stare2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Stare,</orth> vb. 1) to be stiff, to stand on end: <cit><quote>makest . . . my hair to s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.280" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. IV, 3, 280</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) to look with fixed eyes wide open: <bibl n="shak. ven 301" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 301</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ven 301" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 301</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.168" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. V, 5, 168</bibl> (<emph>--ings,</emph> in Evans' speech). <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.927" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 927</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.927" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 927</bibl> <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.230" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 2, 230</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.3.49" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 3, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.3.24" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 V, 3, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.170" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 170</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.170" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 170</bibl> <bibl n="shak. jc 1.3.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 3, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.1.97" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 97</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.40" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 40</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 2.3.110" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. II, 3, 110</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.6.110" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 6, 110</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 5.1.107" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. V, 1, 107</bibl> (Qq <emph>stir</emph>). <bibl n="shak. oth 5.2.188" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 188</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.4.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 4, 5</bibl>. With <cit><quote>on:</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1448" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1448</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. wt 5.2.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 2, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.26" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 7, 26</bibl> (Qq <emph>gazed</emph>). <bibl n="shak. jc 2.1.242" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. II, 1, 242</bibl>. <cit><quote>in her sad face he --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1591" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1591</bibl></cit>. With an accus. expressing the effect: <cit><quote>I will s. him out of his wits,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.2.291" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 2, 291</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>